[src:web-workers/using-web-workers] The exception to this is if the worker script's origin is a globally unique identifier (for example, if its URL has a scheme of data or blob).
[src:web-workers/using-web-workers] In this case, the worker does inherit the CSP of the document or worker that created it.
[src:web-workers/using-web-workers] Data passed between the main page and workers is *copied*, not shared (except for certain objects that can be explicitly shared).
[src:web-workers/using-web-workers] Objects are serialized as they're handed to the worker, and subsequently, de-serialized on the other end.
[src:web-workers/using-web-workers] The page and worker **do not share the same instance**, so the end result is that **a duplicate** is created on each end.
