[src:web-workers/using-web-workers] Transferable objects are transferred from one context to another with a zero-copy operation, which results in a vast performance improvement when sending large data sets.
[src:web-workers/using-web-workers] For example, when transferring an `ArrayBuffer` from your main app to a worker script, the original `ArrayBuffer` is cleared and no longer usable.
[src:web-workers/using-web-workers] Its content is (quite literally) transferred to the worker context.
[src:web-workers/using-web-workers] The `SharedArrayBuffer` object allows two threads, such as the worker and the main thread, to simultaneously operate on the same memory span and exchange data without going through the messaging mechanism.
