[src:web-workers/web-workers-api] A worker is an object created using a constructor (e.g., `Worker()`) that runs a named JavaScript file — this file contains the code that will run in the worker thread.
[src:web-workers/web-workers-api] In addition to the standard JavaScript set of functions (such as `String`, `Array`, `Object`, `JSON`, etc.), you can run almost any code you like inside a worker thread.
[src:web-workers/web-workers-api] There are some exceptions: for example, you can't directly manipulate the DOM from inside a worker, or use some default methods and properties of the `Window` object.
[src:web-workers/web-workers-api] For information about the code that you *can* run see supported functions, and supported Web APIs.
[src:web-workers/web-workers-api] Data is sent between workers and the main thread via a system of messages — both sides send their messages using the `postMessage()` method, and respond to messages via the `onmessage` event handler (the message is contained within the `message` event's `data` property).
[src:web-workers/web-workers-api] Represents a running worker thread, allowing you to pass messages to the running worker code.
[src:web-workers/web-workers-api] Defines the absolute location of the script executed by the `Worker`.
[src:web-workers/web-workers-api] Represents a specific kind of worker that can be accessed from several browsing contexts (i.e., windows, tabs, or iframes) or even other workers.
[src:web-workers/web-workers-api] Represents the generic scope of any worker (doing the same job as `Window` does for normal web content).
[src:web-workers/web-workers-api] Different types of worker have scope objects that inherit from this interface and add more specific features.
[src:web-workers/web-workers-api] Represents the scope of a dedicated worker, inheriting from `WorkerGlobalScope` and adding some dedicated features.
[src:web-workers/web-workers-api] Represents the scope of a shared worker, inheriting from `WorkerGlobalScope` and adding some dedicated features.
[src:web-workers/web-workers-api] Represents the identity and state of the user agent (the client).
[src:web-workers/web-workers-api] You can find out more information on how these demos work in Using Web Workers.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] The **`WorkerGlobalScope`** interface of the Web Workers API is an interface representing the scope of any worker.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Workers have no browsing context; this scope contains the information usually conveyed by `Window` objects — in this case event handlers, the console or the associated `WorkerNavigator` object.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Each `WorkerGlobalScope` has its own event loop.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] This interface is usually specialized by each worker type: `DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope` for dedicated workers, `SharedWorkerGlobalScope` for shared workers, and `ServiceWorkerGlobalScope` for ServiceWorker.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] The `self` property returns the specialized scope for each context.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Returns the `CacheStorage` object associated with the current context.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] This object enables functionality such as storing assets for offline use, and generating custom responses to requests.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Returns a boolean value that indicates whether the website is in a cross-origin isolation state.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Returns the `Crypto` object associated to the global object.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Returns the `FontFaceSet` associated with the worker.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Provides a mechanism for workers to asynchronously access capabilities of indexed databases; returns an `IDBFactory` object.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Returns a boolean indicating whether the current context is secure (`true`) or not (`false`).
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Returns the `WorkerLocation` associated with the worker.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] It is a specific location object, mostly a subset of the `Location` for browsing scopes, but adapted to workers.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Returns the `WorkerNavigator` associated with the worker.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] It is a specific navigator object, mostly a subset of the `Navigator` for browsing scopes, but adapted to workers.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Returns the global object's origin, serialized as a string.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Returns the `Performance` associated with the worker.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Only a subset of the properties and methods of the `Performance` interface are available to workers.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Returns the `Scheduler` object associated with the current context.
