[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Starts the process of fetching a resource from the network.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Imports one or more scripts into the worker's scope.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] You can specify as many as you'd like, separated by commas.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] For example: `importScripts('foo.js', 'bar.js');`.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Queues a microtask to be executed at a safe time prior to control returning to the browser's event loop.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Schedules a function to execute every time a given number of milliseconds elapses.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Schedules a function to execute in a given amount of time.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Creates a deep clone of a given value using the structured clone algorithm.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Reports an error in a script, emulating an unhandled exception.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Fired at the global/worker scope object when the user's preferred languages change.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Fired when the browser has lost access to the network and the value of `navigator.onLine` switched to `false`.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Fired when the browser has gained access to the network and the value of `navigator.onLine` switched to `true`.
[src:web-workers/workerglobalscope] Fired on handled `Promise` rejection events.
